# OpenStatus - Codeium Configuration

## Project Context

OpenStatus: Open-source synthetic monitoring platform
Architecture: pnpm monorepo + Turborepo
Stack: Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Tailwind CSS 4.1, Drizzle ORM, Turso DB

## Critical Rules

1. ALWAYS use pnpm 10.26.0 (never npm/yarn)
2. ALWAYS use Drizzle ORM (never raw SQL)
3. ALWAYS use Biome 1.8.3 for linting (not ESLint)
4. Server Components by default ("use client" only when necessary)
5. React Hook Form + Zod for all forms
6. tRPC for dashboard, Hono for server APIs
7. TypeScript required, avoid 'any'

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase.tsx
- Utilities: camelCase.ts
- Config: kebab-case.ts

## Database
- Schema: packages/db/src/schema/
- Migrations: cd packages/db && pnpm generate
- Never write raw SQL or manual migrations

## Common Commands
pnpm dev:dashboard    # Start dashboard
pnpm format          # Format code
pnpm lint:fix        # Fix linting
pnpm dx              # Setup database

## Forbidden Actions
- Database schema changes without approval
- Auth/payment modifications without approval
- Dockerfile/docker-compose changes
- Raw SQL queries
- Committing secrets
- Major version upgrades
- Manual migrations

